Data Storage:
        aisa kuch jaha pe ham sare users ki info store kar sakte hai
        file - data.txt  --> isme sab kuch store nahi kar sakte

        database -> isme sab kuch store kar sakte hai eg- photos,videos,binary etc.

TYPES OF DBS :- SQL | NoSQL

SQL - data ko ek roop mein rakhna - tables

NoSQL - mongoDB

mongoDB ek database hai jo NoSQL ke concept par kaam karti hai and object ke form mein data store karti hai
data access and store karne ke liye we use it.


terminologies - collections, documents, schemas, keys, models

Backend -> application server(eg - Node) & database server(eg - mongoDB)

application server -> sab kuch karna except data ke kaam se

data wale kaam database servere karta hai



DataBase server ->  

DataBase -> Collection -> DataBase

jo sabse badi identity hai wo hai database and uske andar jo hai wo hai collection ( for eg -> facebook ke database mein likes or username ka collection )

collection me se kisi ek ka database ham dekh rahe hai to wo hai document.


